,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Coal and Steel Community, and in particular  Article 18 thereof,
Whereas by its Decision of 11 June 1993  (1), the Council appointed the members of the Consultative  Committee of the European Coal and Steel Community for the period ending 10  June 1995;
Whereas by its Decision of 31 March 1995  (2), the Council appointed the Austrian, Finnish and  Swedish members of the Consultative Committee of the European Coal and Steel Community;
Whereas by its Decision of 23 October 1995  (3), the Council designated the representative  organizations of producers and workers required to draw up lists of candidates for the  representation of producers and workers on the Consultative Committee of the European Coal and  Steel Community;
Whereas the representative organizations designated by the Decision of 23 October 1995 have  submitted their lists of candidates for the producers and workers categories;
Whereas the Governments of the Member States have submitted their lists of candidates for the  consumers and dealers category;
Whereas the members of the Consultative Committee of the European Coal and Steel Community should  be appointed for a period of two years,
